    "This finding suggests that in scenarios where tasks are challenging for both humans and AI-where the individual performance of humans and AI is relatively low-traditional Explainable AI (XAI) may not improve performance and could even have negative effects.",
    "In contrast, Human-AI Deliberation shows potential to yield positive outcomes, even when the performance of the underlying AI models in these difficult task cases is suboptimal.6.1.2 Reliance.",
    "We measured participants' objective reliance by agreement fraction and switch fraction.",
    "As shown in Figure 7 (a), participants agreed significantly less with AI's suggestions in Deliberative AI (𝑀=0.57, 𝑆𝐷=0.24) than in XAI (𝑀=0.68, 𝑆𝐷=0.27, 𝑝 <0.05), and switched significantly less to AI's predictions in Deliberative AI (𝑀=0.23, 𝑆𝐷=0.35) than in XAI (𝑀=0.51, 𝑆𝐷=0.41, 𝑝 <0.001).",
